  "_comment": "HOSTED config served at FilterConfigStore.remoteURL. Must use a strictly greater configVersion than the app's bundled default to be adopted OTA. Edit selectors here and bump configVersion to push a filter fix with no app update.",
  "_scopeNote": "v1 SCOPE: hide the dedicated infinite reel SURFACES (Reels tab, Explore, YouTube Shorts) - reliable and smooth, and what SocialLite/ScrollGuard actually do. We do NOT delete reels/suggested posts from the HOME timeline: removing a large fraction of an infinite feed makes Instagram's loader spiral (white-out + lag) and the home feed is bounded anyway. The reels_in_feed / suggested features were therefore REMOVED from the shipped config (no footgun toggle). The 'A << B' ancestor mechanism that powered them still exists in feed-filter.js (used by YouTube Shorts) - so if a reliable in-feed approach is found later, those features can be re-introduced via the HOSTED config with no app update. EXPLORE was also removed: on Instagram the magnifying-glass nav IS the Explore link (/explore/), so hiding it also killed Search - which PRD \u00a75.2 requires keeping. A future feature could hide the explore recommendations GRID while preserving the search bar (needs a validated explore-page selector). For now the only Instagram filters are the Reels tab/icon and the 'Open app' button.",
